<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-06-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-06-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="107" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d107">
                    <head>No. 107.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Davis</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Scruggs</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Extract.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-06-30"><hi rend="italic">June</hi> 30,
                            1883</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 72.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 87, of the 30th
                        ultimo, touching the entrance and clearance of American vessels at Panama
                        and Colon, and I desire to express the Department’s pleasure at the prompt
                        acquiescence of the Colombian Government in the views set forth in your note
                        to the minister for foreign affairs, which is approved.* * *</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <closer><signed>JNO. DAVIS,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Acting
                            Secretary.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>